{
  "slug": "learn_springboot",
  "title": "Learn Spring Boot for Back-end development",
  "description": "Start your backend development journey with Spring Boot, a powerful Java-based framework designed to simplify building production-grade applications. Learn the core concepts like RESTful APIs, dependency injection, and application configuration, and see how to connect with databases using JPA and Hibernate. As you progress, dive into real-world features like validation, error handling, and layered architecture. Perfect for Java beginners, this hands-on path helps you move from writing simple endpoints to building complete backend systems — all with minimal setup and maximum productivity.",
  "modules": [
    {
      "name": "Spring Boot Fundamentals",
      "description": "This module covers the basics of Spring Boot, a powerful framework that simplifies Java application development. Learn the difference between Spring and Spring Boot, the idea of convention over configuration, and how to handle XML/JSON, use Hibernate/Spring Data JPA, and manage dependencies with Maven. You’ll also build your first Spring Boot app, understand @SpringBootApplication, and run it using main() or mvn spring-boot:run.",
