    {
      "name": "Clean Architecture & Full CRUD (In-Memory)",
      "description": "In this module, you will refactor your application using Clean Architecture principles and implement full CRUD operations in an in-memory setup. You’ll learn why putting all logic in the controller causes tight coupling and maintenance issues, and how Layered Architecture (Controller -> Service -> Repository) solves this with proper separation of concerns. You’ll also understand interface-based design for loose coupling and build complete CRUD APIs using POST, GET, PUT, and DELETE.",
